built confessional box and most times the confessional had the facility of using both sides of the confessional \u2022 Catholics use to make the sign of the cross whenever they passed in front of a Catholic church \u2022 You had to genuflect properly before entering a pew These are some of the traditions and practices which used to be the norm 50 years ago in this Archdiocese Many of these are no longer , or at most sparsely used in today \u2019s Church Whether they have disappeared for good or there is a possibility of their return is open to speculation", "date": "2012-09-02T06:16:53", "feat": {"popular": 2, "do": 1, "time": 2, "deceased": 1, "church": 4}, "embersId": "d614156a41dbde48a653a63d9096972e48bd8269"}
